sql:
SELECT MAX(access_date) AS last_access_date
FROM user_stock_access
WHERE user_id = 1 AND stock_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "risen the most in value" refers to the highest percentage change in closing price; 
- "past month" refers to the last 30 days; 
- "biggest fan" refers to the user who has created the most alerts for each stock.

sql:
SELECT user_id, MAX(access_date) AS last_access_date
FROM user_stock_access
GROUP BY user_id;
